parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective dashboard material can cause the dashboard to become sticky and gummy, crack, and chip, which can be a distraction to the driver and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard becomes sticky and gummy
the dashboard cracks and chips without cause or reason
the dashboard defects appear within a short period of owning the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine acceleration and stalling problems can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle has acceleration problems
the vehicle stalls periodically
the vehicle has been in the shop multiple times for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of control and visibility while driving.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without an actual collision
loud explosion
strong gunpowder odor
torn airbag
whitened front windshield
inability to see the road
seatbelts locking
and a sense of shock and disorientation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Powertrain Control Module (PCM) can cause the vehicle to fail to shift gears properly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift gears properly
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle experiences unusual or erratic shifting patterns
the vehicle's engine RPMs fluctuate erratically
the vehicle's speedometer or odometer malfunctions.
